<header>
	In the previous exercise we saw that Alexandra didn't really pay attention to the topic in Part 2. Which of the following would you suggest to improve Alexandra's performance?
</header>
	
<section id="body">
	<img class="rightFloat" src="../Media/MM_SP_005.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"  /><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000"><g id="1">A. Talk more about the subject in general.</g></font></p><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000"><g id="2">B. Read the instructions carefully.</g></font></p><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000"><g id="3">C. Find out what to expect in each part of the test.</g></font></p><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000"><g id="4">D. Ask the examiner for more information.</g></font></p><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000"><g id="5">E. Learn more about advertising and other popular topics.</g></font></p><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000"><g id="6">F. Consider taking notes to sort out her thoughts.</g></font></p><p align="left"><font size="2"></font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb1">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">Speaking more generally would not help.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb2">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">Yes. You will never answer the question correctly unless you read the instructions carefully.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb3">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">This will help you to prepare properly, and will increase your confidence.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb4">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">She had all the information she needed on the card.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb5">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">Her knowledge was not the problem here.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb6">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">Notes will help you to keep going, and will also prevent you from straying from the topic.</font></p>
</section>
